    <abstract>
      <t>Encrypted Key Transport (EKT) is an extension to DTLS and Secure Real-time Transport Protocol (SRTP) that provides for the secure transport of SRTP master keys, rollover counters, and other information within SRTP. This facility enables SRTP for decentralized conferences by distributing a common key to all of the conference endpoints.</t>
